   "body" : "Use SipHash-2-4 for:\r\n* CCoinsViewCache hashmap (instead of a custom Lookup3/XOR scheme)\r\n* CTxMempool::mapTx txid index (converting from an ordered map)\r\n* Address relay peer selection (instead of SHA256)\r\n\r\nComputing a hash for a txid using this takes around 40 CPU cycles in benchmarks (the Lookup3/XOR based mechanism used for CCoinsViewCache took 25 cycles). I think that's negligible still, while using a much more standard construct designed for such purposes.\r\n",
